  "prompt": "Who was the Guru of Guru Nanak Dev Ji?",
  "response": "According to historical accounts, Guru Nanak Dev Ji did not have a formal guru in the traditional sense. He was spiritually inspired and guided by his own inner wisdom and divine connection. He was known for rejecting religious orthodoxy and seeking spiritual truth directly through meditation and contemplation.\n\nHowever, some historical sources suggest that Guru Nanak Dev Ji was influenced by spiritual teachers and traditions of his time, including:\n\n1. His father, Mehta Kalu, who introduced him to basic spiritual teachings\n\n2. Spiritual masters from various traditions like Hindu and Muslim saints\n\n3. Spiritual traditions of Bhakti and Sufi movements\n\nUltimately, Guru Nanak Dev Ji is considered to have received divine guidance directly from God, whom he referred to as the Supreme Guru. He emphasized direct spiritual experience over formal religious rituals and institutional structures.\n\nHis spiritual teachings were based on his own profound mystical experiences and insights, which formed the foundation of Sikhism. He preached the principles of equality, universal brotherhood, and devotion to the one formless God.",
